              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " A storage-cell cryostat filled by liquid 4He at",
                " liquid-N2 temperature. Target cell was made of",
                " 80 micron thick Kapton foil with diameter of 90 mm",
                " and a height of 75 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "QMPH",
                  "TAGD"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Quasimonoenergetic photons from",
                "bremsstrahlung tagging facility."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two large solid-angle neutron detectors,",
                " each consisting of 3 x 3 array on 9 rectangular cells",
                " with internal dimensions 20 cm x 20 cm (deep) filled",
                " with the liquid scintillator NEA2132A."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight spectrometer consisted of liquid",
                " and plastic scintillators."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SHAPE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Pulse-shape discrimination was employed to",
                "distinguish neutrons from random photons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical uncertainties."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainty was dominated by",
                " the systematic uncertainty in the neutron-detection",
                " efficiency, which ranged from ~ 5% for Eg = 68.5 MeV",
                " to 26% for Eg = 24.6 MeV. Other large sources of",
                " uncertainty were:",
                "  *  the neutron-inscattering correction(~ 9%),",
                "  *  the neutron-yield attenuation correction (~ 6%),",
                "  *  the number of photons (a combination of the",
                "     tagger focal-plane live time and the tagging",
                "     efficiency; ~ 4%):",
                " Value Uncertainty (%)",
                " Kinematic-dependent quantity",
                "  Neutron-detection efficiency     0.20       8.",
                "  Neutron inscattering             1.25       9.",
                "  Neutron-yield attenuation        0.85       6.",
                "  Tagger focal-plane live time     0.95       2.",
                "  Neutron-detector live time       0.50       1.",
                "  Photon-beam attenuation        (in text)  < 1.",
                " Scale quantity",
                "  Tagging efficiency               0.25       3.",
                "  Geometrical acceptance         (in text)    2.",
                "  Target density                 (in text)    2.",
                "  Particle misidentification     (in text)  < 1."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A comprehensive 4He(g,n) absolute cross section",
                " measurements was performed at MAX-lab in Lund. Tagged",
                " photons from 23 < Eg < 70 MeV were directed toward a",
                " liquid 4He target, and neutrons were identified using",
                " pulse-shape discrimination and the time-of-flight",
                " technique in two liquid-scintillator detectors",
                " arrays. Seven-point angular distributions were",
                " measured for 14 photon energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
